            number: 4,
            title: "Add a weekly review of your tracking data — five minutes, three questions",
            description: "Once per week, during your regular weekly review, spend five minutes reviewing the past week's tracking data and answering three questions: What was my completion rate for each behavioral commitment this week? What specific circumstances led to any missed days? What one adjustment would most improve next week's completion rate? The weekly review converts raw tracking data into actionable insight — it is the processing step that transforms measurement into course correction. Without this weekly synthesis, tracking data accumulates as a historical record without generating the behavioral guidance that gives tracking its value. The questions are brief and specific enough to complete in five minutes without turning the review into a lengthy self-analysis session."
          },
