            number: 5,
            title: "Add a qualitative dimension to at least one metric",
            description: "For your most important behavioral commitment, supplement the binary completion tracking with a one-sentence qualitative rating immediately after each session: the quality of focus during the writing session (1-10), the intensity of the workout (1-10), the depth of engagement during the study session (1-10). This sentence-length qualitative addition captures the Goodhart's Law correction — it distinguishes days when the metric was technically met from days when the behavior was genuinely performed at a quality that advances the goal. Review both the quantitative completion rate and the qualitative rating distribution in your weekly review to identify patterns: are high-quality sessions concentrated on specific days? Are low-quality sessions correlated with poor sleep or late scheduling? These correlations are the most actionable data your tracking system can generate."
          },
