            number: 6,
            title: "Celebrate milestones explicitly — 30, 60, 90 days",
            description: "At each major milestone — 30, 60, and 90 consecutive days of consistent behavioral tracking — pause to explicitly acknowledge the streak. Write a brief milestone note in your tracking journal, share the milestone with your accountability partner, or mark it visibly on your physical tracker. The milestone acknowledgment is not performative; it serves a specific function. Research on goal pursuit by Fishbach and colleagues found that acknowledging progress at midpoints is specifically associated with increased motivation and commitment to goal completion — the milestone acknowledgment renews motivational engagement at the points when it is most likely to flag. The 30-day milestone is particularly critical: it coincides with the period when the initial novelty motivation has faded and the habit has not yet achieved full automaticity — precisely when explicit milestone recognition provides the most motivational value."
          }
        ]} />
